snippet.textDisplay: So I'm from France, and years ago I brought a creme egg for my 7 year old sister back home. I was about to tell her that the chocolate is deceptively thick and that there's goo inside, and to take a bite of it first. But the little glutton stuck the whole thing in her mouth and bit down. What ensued was traumatic. First, the look of shock in her eyes, then terror set in when she realised her mouth was essentially sealed shut with goo. She struggled to take a breath, her eyes grew wider in horror and a single tear game down. I was urging her to spit it out, SPIT IT OUT! I cried. But she carried on like a brave little soldier and managed to eat. I tell you, that first breath felt like victory to her. I no longer bring creme eggs on my vistits home.
